    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-root",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "🧩 Edge Class Contract (Normative)",
      "position": {
        "x": 140,
        "y": 160
      },
      "width": 780,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Edge Class Contract\n\n**Authority:** Normative\n\nAn **edge class** is the canonical reusable bundle for:\n- relationship *meaning*\n- rendering defaults\n- legend identity and preview\n\nThis contract exists to make edge class authoring (Tutorial Step 2) *specific and testable*, and to ensure the same edge class renders consistently in:\n- graph canvas\n- legend previews\n- edge properties preview\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-identity",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "1. Identity (Required)",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 520
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## 1. Identity Contract (REQUIRED)\n\nA valid edge class artifact MUST provide stable identity and a human-facing label.\n\nCanonical storage (node-first):\n- Create **Field** nodes.\n- For each field node, set:\n  - `title` (a path like `edgeClass.key`)\n  - `fieldType` (usually `string`)\n  - `value`\n\nRequired titles:\n- `edgeClass.key` (stable key, e.g. `task.depends-on`)\n- `edgeClass.label` (human label)\n- `edgeClass.meaning` (one-line semantics)\n\nAdditional recommended identity (graph-level):\n- Declaration/manifest may still set `identity.graphId` / `identity.name` / `identity.description`, but edge class values are authored as nodes.\n\nRule:\n- `edgeClass.key` is the *primary stable key*.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-render",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "2. Render Defaults (Required)",
      "position": {
        "x": 300,
        "y": 520
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 420,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## 2. Render Defaults Contract (REQUIRED)\n\nAn edge class MUST declare its canonical style in a single place, so every renderer and preview can match.\n\nCanonical storage (node-first):\n- Create Field nodes with:\n  - `title`: `renderDefaults.stroke` (fieldType: `string`, value: hex color)\n  - `title`: `renderDefaults.width` (fieldType: `number`, value: a number)\n\nOptional:\n- `renderDefaults.dash` (fieldType: `json`, value: `[22, 8]`)\n- `renderDefaults.routingHint` (string, e.g. `orthogonal`)\n- `renderDefaults.labelTone` (string, e.g. `accent`)\n\nRule:\n- render defaults are the single source of truth for legend preview and edge rendering.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-preview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "3. Preview (Required Behavior)",
      "position": {
        "x": 960,
        "y": 520
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 420,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## 3. Preview Contract (REQUIRED BEHAVIOR)\n\nThe legend preview MUST visually match the on-canvas edge.\n\nPreferred implementation rule:\n- Preview SVG is **derived** from `renderDefaults`.\n\nAllowed fallback:\n- A stored sample SVG may exist, but it MUST be treated as decorative unless validated against `renderDefaults`.\n\nRule:\n- Drift between legend preview and on-canvas edge is a contract violation.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-views",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "4. Views (Recommended Minimum)",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 880
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## 4. Views Contract (RECOMMENDED MINIMUM)\n\n### A) Stable view names (CONTRACT)\nThese payloads are the stable API for discovery + selection:\n- `node.web.icon`\n- `node.web.summary` (port-consumable default)\n- `node.web.detail`\n- `node.web.document`\n- `editor.web` (editors only)\n\n### B) Minimum surfaces (EDGE CLASS)\nAn edge class artifact MUST expose:\n- a **summary surface** with payload `node.web.summary`\n\nIt SHOULD also expose:\n- `icon-view` with payload `node.web.icon`\n- `node-view` with payload `node.web.detail`\n\nNotes:\n- Ports are **view consumers**. They do not provide views; they select among exposed surfaces (or fall back to minimap).\n- The node type can vary (`summary-view`, legacy `port-view`, etc.) as long as the payload matches the contract.\n- Class usability (legend/type selector) is primarily driven by bridge export + `edgeClass` Field nodes.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-export",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "5. Export Surface (Library Declaration)",
      "position": {
        "x": 300,
        "y": 980
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 420,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## 5. Export Surface Contract (REQUIRED FOR CONSUMPTION)\n\nEdge classes are consumed from a **library export surface**.\n\nCurrent canonical example:\n- `/library/classes/edges/root.node#root`\n\nLibrary declaration MUST:\n- declare `kind: library`\n- define an export surface (e.g. `surfaces[].kind = export`)\n- expose `edgeClasses` via allow/allowlist\n\nConsumer bridge MUST:\n- target the library\n- select the export surface (if surface selection is enabled)\n- have `Create` grant\n\nRule:\n- Edge classes do not become available just because the graph is reachable; they must be exported.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-assignment",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "6. Assignment + Precedence",
      "position": {
        "x": 960,
        "y": 980
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 420,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## 6. Edge Assignment Contract\n\nA plain edge remains valid without a class.\n\nWhen an edge is classified, it SHOULD store:\n- `edge.data.edgeClassRef` (authoritative)\n- `edge.data.edgeClassKey` (stable key mirror)\n\nPrecedence (render):\n1. instance overrides (`edge.style`, explicit instance `type`)\n2. class defaults (`edgeClass.renderDefaults`, `edgeClass.defaultEdgeType`)\n3. fallback: plain line\n\nRule:\n- semantics live in the class. Instance `label` is display metadata.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-step-2-checklist",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2 Checklist (Concrete)",
      "position": {
        "x": 140,
        "y": 1440
      },
      "width": 1080,
      "height": 520,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Tutorial Step 2: Concrete Authoring Checklist\n\nTo complete Step 2, author the edge class as **nodes**, not nested JSON.\n\nFor each Field node, set:\n- `title`\n- `fieldType`\n- `value`\n\n### A) Identity (required)\nCreate Field nodes:\n- `edgeClass.key` (string)\n- `edgeClass.label` (string)\n- `edgeClass.meaning` (string)\n\n### B) Render defaults (required)\nCreate Field nodes:\n- `renderDefaults.stroke` (string hex)\n- `renderDefaults.width` (number)\n\nOptional:\n- `renderDefaults.dash` (json, e.g. `[22, 8]`)\n- `renderDefaults.routingHint` (string)\n\n### C) Port-consumable summary view (REQUIRED)\n- Add a `summary-view` (or legacy `port-view`) node with:\n  - `payload`: `node.web.summary`\n\n### D) Optional semantics\nCreate Field nodes (optional):\n- `defaultEdgeType` (string)\n- `sourceKinds` (json array or CSV string)\n- `targetKinds` (json array or CSV string)\n\n### E) Preview correctness\n- The legend preview MUST match the render defaults (no drift).\n\n### F) Export\n- Ensure the edge class library export surface allowlists your `edgeClass.key`.\n\nPass criteria:\n- The class appears in the consumer legend/type selector and renders identically on canvas.\n"
      }
    }
  ],
